Definitely a good restaurant for take out but has an intimate and relaxed environment that's worth sticking around for.

This is a teency, family-owned restaurant with nice people and great food. I never know what to get, so I always ask for a recommendation and have not been disappointed yet. If you like spicy, great, because they'll warn you that even their mild is a little more spicy than most.

Great to fine an affordable, authentic Indian restaurant in our neighborhood! The staff was very accommodating and checked in many times to make sure we liked the spiciness level of our food. If you like spicy, this is a great place to try! Very unassuming but a cute spot with good food.

Incredible food! Naan was light, doughy, and fresh. We had the mango curry chicken and the sag paneer, both were outstanding. So glad I found this gem so closeby!
